('All Night', 'Em All Night, Beyoncé explora a dor da traição e o caminho da reconciliação, mostrando que o perdão nasce do enfrentamento honesto das feridas e da escolha consciente de reconstruir a confiança. A letra e os arranjos reforçam a renovação emocional e física do relacionamento, enquanto o sample de OutKast acrescenta uma dimensão nostálgica. A música celebra vulnerabilidade, superação e a decisão de permanecer, transformando imperfeições em símbolos de amor resiliente.', 2, 4, '5:22', 'I found the truth beneath your lies And true love never has to hide (True love never has to hide) I''ll trade your broken wings for mine (Trade your broken wings for mine) oh I''ve seen your scars and kissed your crime (Seen your scars and kissed your crime) oh-oh-oh So many people that I know, they''re just tryna touch ya Kiss up and rub up and feel up Kiss up and rub up and feel up on you Give you some time to prove that I can trust you again I''m gonna kiss up and rub up and feel up Kiss up and rub up and feel up on you All night long Sweet love all night long Sweet love (sweet love) all night long Sweet love all night long You''re all I wanna Ain''t no other We together I remember Sweet love all night long Our love was stronger than your pride Beyond your darkness, I''m your light, oh If you get deep, you''ll touch my mind (If you get deep, you''ll touch my mind) oh Baptize your tears and dry your eyes (Baptize your tears and dry your eyes) oh-oh-oh-oh So many people, I know that they''re just tryna touch ya Kiss up and rub up and feel up Kiss up and rub up and feel up on you Give you some time to prove that I can trust you again I''m gonna kiss up and rub up and feel up Kiss up and rub up and feel up on you All night long Sweet love all night long Sweet love all night long Sweet love all night long You''re all I wanna Ain''t no other (ain''t no other) We together (we together) I remember (I remember) Sweet love all night long They say true love''s the greatest weapon 