('BREAK MY SOUL', 'BREAK MY SOUL é um hino de libertação pessoal e coletiva, que transforma a exaustão profissional e a pressão social em um chamado para o autocuidado. A repetição de (You won''t break my soul) transmite resiliência e o refrão (I''m telling everybody) fortalece a união. A música critica a rotina de trabalho opressiva e celebra a busca por bem-estar, com versos como (I just quit my job) representando a escolha de romper com o ciclo. Com samples de Robin S. e Big Freedia, a faixa também se conecta à tradição de empoderamento das pistas de dança, incentivando todos a priorizarem sua saúde mental e felicidade.', 2, 5, '4:38', '(I''m ''bout to explode, take off this load) (Bend it, bust it open, won''t ya make it go?) (Yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka) (Yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka) (Release your wiggle) (Yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka) (Yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka, yaka) (Release your wiggle) Ah, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la La, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la You won''t break my soul You won''t break my soul You won''t break my soul You won''t break my soul I''m telling everybody Everybody, everybody, everybody Now, I just fell in love, and I just quit my job I''m gonna find new drive, damn, they work me so damn hard Work by nine, then off past five And they work my nerves, that''s why I cannot sleep at night Motivation I''m looking for a new foundation, yeah And I''m on that new vibration I''m building my own foundation, yeah Hold up, oh, baby, baby You won''t brеak my soul (na, na) You won''t break my soul (no, no, na, na) You won''t break my soul (no, no, na, na) You won''t break my soul (na, na) I''m tеlling everybody (na, na) Everybody, everybody, everybody (Release your anger, release your mind) (Release your job, release the time) (Release your trade, release the stress) (Release the love, forget the rest) I''ma let down my hair ''cause I lost my mind Bey is back and I''m sleeping