('SUMMER RENAISSANCE', 'SUMMER RENAISSANCE fecha o álbum com uma nota de otimismo e celebração. A música evoca a sensação de um verão eterno, utilizando samples do icônico sucesso disco I Feel Love, de Donna Summer, o que reforça o clima de festa, liberdade e nostalgia. A letra é focada na autoconfiança e na capacidade de se sentir bem e invencível, marcando o clímax da jornada de empoderamento e redescoberta do disco.', 2, 5, '6:28', 'I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, ride, ride) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, ride, ride) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, ride, ride) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, ride, ride) Oh-ooh-oh-ooh-ooh-oh-ooh Oh-ooh-oh-ooh-ooh-oh-ooh Oh-ooh-oh-ooh-ooh-oh-ooh Oh-ooh-oh-ooh-ooh-oh-ooh (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) I''m feeling it (I''m feeling it) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) This ain''t no drill (this ain''t no drill) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, ride, ride) I''m gonna ride to the end of the world (ride, 