('Bad Blood', 'A música fala sobre a dor causada por uma traição dentro de uma amizade, mostrando como a confiança pode ser destruída de forma profunda. Taylor Swift se inspirou em um conflito real com outra artista que tentou prejudicar sua turnê, o que explica a intensidade do tema. As metáforas de cortes e cicatrizes reforçam o quanto a atitude da outra pessoa deixou marcas emocionais difíceis de superar.', 3, 8, '3:31', '''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood You know, it used to be mad love So take a look what you''ve done ''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Now we got problems And I don''t think we can solve ''em You made a really deep cut And, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Did you have to do this? I was thinking that you could be trusted Did you have to ruin What was shining? Now, it''s all rusted Did you have to hit me Where I''m weak? Baby, I couldn''t breathe And rub it in so deep Salt in the wound, like you''re laughing right at me Oh, it''s so sad to Think about the good times You and I ''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood You know, it used to be mad love So take a look what you''ve done ''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Now we got problems And I don''t think we can solve ''em You made a really deep cut And, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Did you think we''d be fine? Still got scars on my back from your knife So don''t think it''s in the past These kinda wounds, they last, and they last Now, did you think it all through? All these things will catch up to you And time can heal, but this won''t So if you''re coming my way, just don''t Oh, it''s so sad to Think about the good times You and I ''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood You know, it used to be mad love So take a look what you''ve done ''Cause, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Now we got problems And I don''t think we can solve ''em You made a really deep cut And, baby, now we got bad blood, hey Band-Aids don''t fix bullet holes You say sorry just for show If you live like that, you live wit