('intro (End of the World)', 'Em intro (end of the world), Ariana Grande explora dúvidas internas sobre amor e relacionamentos, refletindo sobre a dificuldade de distinguir sentimentos verdadeiros e a incerteza quanto ao futuro afetivo. A música cria uma atmosfera introspectiva e vulnerável, alinhada ao tema central do álbum Eternal Sunshine, que valoriza a autoanálise e a reflexão emocional.', 10, 29, '1:32', 'Uh How can I tell if I''m in the right relationship? Aren''t you really supposed to know that shit? Feel it in your bones and own that shit? I don''t know Then I had this interaction I''ve been thinkin'' ''bout for like five weeks Wonder if he''s thinkin'' ''bout it too and smiling Wonder if he knows that that''s been what''s inspirin'' me Wonder if he''s judgin'' me like I am right now I don''t care I''d rather tell the truth Than make it worse for you, mm If the Sun refused to shine Baby, would I still be your lover? Would you want me there? If the Moon went dark tonight And if it all ended tomorrow Would I be the one on your mind, your mind, your mind? And if it all ended tomorrow Would you be the one on mine?'),
('bye', 'Em bye, Ariana Grande combina uma sonoridade disco animada com a temática do término de um relacionamento, criando um contraste entre ritmo dançante e mensagem de despedida. A música transmite uma ruptura madura e respeitosa, sem mágoa ou ressentimento, enfatizando a escolha consciente de encerrar a relação com empatia e equilíbrio emocional.', 10, 29, '2:44', 'Bye-bye Boy, bye, hmm Hmm Bye-bye Boy, bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah This ain''t the first time I''ve been hostage to these tears I can''t believe I''m finally movin'' through my fears At least I know how hard we tried, both you and me Didn''t we? Didn''t we? So I grab my stuff Courtney just pulled up in the driveway It''s time Bye-bye Boy, bye Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Bye-bye I''m takin'' what''s mine, yeah Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah You know, I''m stronger than I think Usually, I''d join you on the floor, but this dance ain''t for me Boy, just turn the music up Maybe, someday we''ll look back with love Didn''t think you''d lose me Now it''s just too late to choose me So I grab my stuff Courtney just pulled up in the driveway It''s time Bye-bye Boy, bye Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Bye-bye I''m takin'' what''s mine, yeah Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Now, it''s certainly bittersweet This hook feels too hard to sing But it''s better than repeat Bye-bye Boy, bye Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Bye-bye I''m takin'' what''s mine, yeah Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Bye-bye Boy, bye Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah Bye-bye I''m takin'' what''s mine, yeah Bye-bye It''s over, it''s over, oh, yeah'),
('don''t wanna break up again', 'Em don’t wanna break up again, Ariana Grande aborda a fragilidade emocional de quem se vê preso em ciclos repetidos de término e reconciliação. A música evidencia a dificuldade de romper de vez devido à ligação afetiva e à culpa compartilhada, refletindo a complexidade de um relacionamento indefinido, onde ambos sabem que o fim é necessário, mas a conexão emocional impede a decisão final.', 10, 29, '2:54', 'Mm I fall asleep cryin'' You turn up the TV You don''t wanna hear me One more sleepless night Big day in the morning So I take my time to self-soothe I''m too much for you So I really gotta do The thing I don''t wanna do No, I don''t, don''t, don''t, don''t I don''t wanna fuck with your head It''s breakin'' my heart To keep breakin'' yours again This situationship has to end But I just can''t refuse I don''t wanna break up again, baby I made it so easy Spent so much on therapy Blamed my own codependency But you didn''t even try When you finally did, it was at the wrong time Won''t abandon me again for you and I, I I''m too much for you So I really gotta do The thing I don''t wanna do No, I don''t, don''t, don''t, don''t I don''t wanna fuck with your head It''s breakin'' my heart To keep breakin'' yours again This situationship has to end But I just can''t refuse I don''t wanna break up again We both know it''s time So we say goodbye Just one kiss goodbye With tears in our eyes Hope you won''t, won''t regret me Hope you''ll still think fondly of our little life I don''t wanna fuck with your head It''s breakin'' my heart To keep breakin'' yours again This situationship has to end But I just can''t refuse I don''t wanna break up again, baby I don''t wanna break up again I don''t wanna, baby Situationship has to end Just can''t refuse'),
('Saturn Returns Interlude', 'Em Saturn Returns Interlude, Ariana Grande utiliza um monólogo astrológico para simbolizar um ponto de virada no álbum Eternal Sunshine. A narrativa de Diana Garland destaca o retorno de Saturno como um chamado à maturidade, responsabilidade e autoconhecimento, incentivando a artista (e o ouvinte) a deixar ilusões e zonas de conforto para trás, sinalizando uma evolução pessoal em relação a trabalhos anteriores.', 10, 29, '0:42', 'When we''re all born, Saturn''s somewhere And the Saturn cycle takes around about twenty-nine years That''s when we gotta wake up and smell the coffee Because if we''ve just been sort of relying on our cleverness Or relying, you know, just kind of floating along Saturn comes along and hits you over the head Hits you over the head, hits you over the head, and says: Wake up Aha, it''s time for you to get real about life and sort out who you really are Wake up Get real'),
('eternal sunshine', 'Em eternal sunshine, Ariana Grande referencia o filme Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind para explorar a tensão entre lembrar e esquecer um relacionamento passado. A música aborda o desejo de apagar memórias dolorosas como forma de aliviar o sofrimento, refletindo a luta interna entre a dor da lembrança e a tentativa de buscar alívio emocional, mostrando que, mesmo querendo esquecer, o impacto emocional dessas experiências permanece.', 10, 29, '3:30', 'I I don''t care what people say We both know I couldn''t change you I guess you could say the same Can''t rearrange truth I''ve never seen someone lie like you do So much, even you start to think it''s true, ooh Get me out of this loop Yeah, yeah So now we play our separate scenes Now, now she''s in my bed, layin'' on your chest Now I''m in my head, wonderin'' how it ends I''ll be the first to say: I''m sorry Now you got me feelin'' sorry I showed you all my demons, all my lies Yet, you played me like Atari Now it''s like I''m lookin'' in the mirror Hope you feel alright when you''re in her I found a good boy and he''s on my side You''re just my eternal sunshine, sunshine So I try to wipe my mind Just so I feel less insane Rather feel painless I''d rather forget than know, know for sure What we could''ve fought through behind this door, mm-mm So I close it and move, yeah, yeah So now we play our separate scenes Now, now he''s in your bed and layin'' on my chest Now I''m in my head, i''m wonderin'' how it ends, ends, ends I''ll be the first to say: I''m sorry Now you got me feelin'' sorry I showed you all my demons, all my lies Yet, you played me like Atari Now it''s like I''m lookin'' in the mirror Hope you feel alright when you''re in her I found a good boy and he''s on my side You''re just my eternal sunshine, sunshine Won''t break, can''t shake This fate, rewrite Deep breaths, tight chest Life, death, rewind Won''t break, can''t shake This fate, rewrite Deep breaths, tight chest Life, death